mart as the players we'll never win because they have what sometimes seems like unlimited mana and hitpoints that make a buffed warrior look like fire beetle.  What we're talking about isn't whether or not the encounters become undoable, we're talking about whether they are worth the massive amount of time that will be spent doing CR.  I started playing EQ on the day it was released to the public, and it was a great game.  My shaman reached L50 before the Kunark rumors ever started.  I got bored, Verant started rewriting the rules a little bit at a time, so I sold the account and bid them good riddance.  Six months later I bought Kunark and started playing again.  Having known at least a little about the uber encounters (or at least the 'classic' ones) I always remembered never having enough warriors to pull them off.  So, I start a warrior and level him up to L53.  Now I knew warrior taunt got weaker as he approached L50, but it was still usable.  Already at L53 I get to group with rangers who think they are warriors who enjoy nuking, snaring, DoTing until I can't even do my job anymore.  What am I to do?  Ruin their fun by telling them to stop casting spells?  So my frustration was already building.  Now this new patch, and the only hope for keeping the cleric alive now is a hybrid, half-ass tank DoTing, DDing, and basically casting everything they've got to pull crap off the cleric after which of course I can never regain the MOBs attention.  Now the efficiency of the fight has gone down the toilet since the half-tank is taking more damage than I would, has less HPs that I do making CH less efficient.  So now we're sitting out out butts at the end of a fight waiting on mana again.  Exactly the reason we group in the first place, to cut downtime to a minimum.  Of course, I'm just talking about single group fighting to say nothing of these new uber raids which I haven't even had the chance to experience.  The problem isn't that they are making changes, change can be good.  Making people re-evaluate their tactics is good.  However, completely re-writing the rules of the game throws everything out the window.  Here you spend all this time playing this character only to have your role changed to something you no longer find enjoyable.<br>
<br>
Of course, as long as you are willing to keep taking it up the ass from Verant, they're not going to change anything.  If you're smart you'll stop going on uber raids.  When they see that we're simply not going to try if they keep re-writing the rules on us, they'll either fix it or we'll get tired of never having anything to do (again) and quit.</td></tr></table><br><p>[ No Comments Allowed for Anonymous, please <a href="user.php">register</a>  | <a href="comments.php?sid=77&pid=345&mode=&order=&thold=">Parent</a> ]</font><p><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=414&sid=77&pid=412&mode=&order=&thold=#414">Re: Sad day for Everquest</a> by Senex <font size=2>on Saturday, February 24 @ 03:42:15 EST</font><br><ul><li><a href="comments.php?op=showreply&tid=449&sid=77&pid=414&mode=&order=&thold=#449">You are a MORON</a> by Anonymous <font size=2>on Monday, February 26 @ 10:43:37 EST</font><br></ul></ul></p></td><td bgcolor=ffffff><img src=themes/NukeNews/pixel.gif width=10 height=1 border=0></td></tr></table>

